  • Method Details

    • isAllocatable

      public boolean isAllocatable()
      Returns true when this exchange can be allocated to a product output or waste input, thus it is either a product input, waste output, or elementary flow (and not an avoided product or waste flow).

    • hasUncertainty

      public boolean hasUncertainty()
      Returns true when the exchange has an uncertainty distribution assigned.

    • isElementary

      public boolean isElementary()
      Returns true if the flow of this exchange is an elementary flow.

    • isLinkable

      public boolean isLinkable()
      Returns true if this exchange can be linked to a provider. This is the case if this exchange is a product input or waste output.
